        "subject": "LU-3936 ldlm: prevent overflow when counting granded resources",
        "message": "LU-3936 ldlm: prevent overflow when counting granded resources\n\nWhen the total amount of resources we may release counted the\ntotal value can overflow integer.\n\n    int total = 0, cached = 0;\n\n    for (nr_ns = ldlm_namespace_nr_read(client);\n         nr_ns > 0; nr_ns--)\n    {\n        [...]\n        total += ldlm_pool_shrink(&ns->ns_pool, 0, gfp_mask);\n        [...]\n        cached += ldlm_pool_granted(&ns->ns_pool);\n        [...]\n    }\n\nSigned-off-by: Dmitry Eremin <dmitry.eremin@intel.com>\nChange-Id: Icd534806d54f66bffc4eaa13ad1fcd188dfdc6ff\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
